## Key design notes

- **True sliding window** — every request timestamp is stored individually; on each call we prune `<= now - windowMs` and count what remains. No fixed-interval reset.
- **`X-RateLimit-Reset` / `Retry-After`** are computed from the *oldest in-window timestamp* (`oldest + windowMs`), i.e. the moment a slot actually frees — not an arbitrary clock boundary.
