- **Proxies** — documented in the header comment: enable `app.set('trust proxy', ...)` only when you control the proxy chain, since `X-Forwarded-For` is spoofable otherwise.

One scaling caveat worth flagging: this stores state in process memory, so it's per-instance. Behind multiple Node workers/servers each has its own window — for a shared global limit you'd back `hits` with Redis (e.g. a sorted set per key using the same prune-and-count logic).

